# sent_id = perry-260-s2
# text = Λύκον δὲ γαυρωθέντα καρτερὸς λέων ἑλὼν κατήσθι'· ὁ δ' ἐβόησε μετανοῶν· "Οἴησις ἡμῖν πημάτων παραιτία."
# parallel_id = lyceum-aesop-p260/s2
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = But a strong lion, having seized the swaggering wolf, devoured him; and he cried out, repenting: "Conceit is the cause of our troubles."
# literal_translation = A wolf but having been puffed up a strong lion having seized devoured; he but cried out repenting; Conceit to us of troubles the cause.
